    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/rfcs/pull/47\">PR #47</a> from <code>alexcrichton:rm-wasi-threads</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Delete the implementation of the [wasi-threads] proposal from Wasmtime, namely the <code>wasmtime-wasi-threads</code> and <code>wasi-common</code> crates, along with the <code>-Sthreads</code> CLI flag. Uses cases that need any threading at all for portability will be served in the near term with WASIp3 cooperative threads, and long-term support for true multithreading will be best served through the [shared-everything-threads] proposal.</p>\n<p>[wasi-threads]: <a href=\"https://github.com/webassembly/wasi-threads\">https://github.com/webassembly/wasi-threads</a><br>\n[shared-everything-threads]: <a href=\"https://github.com/webassembly/shared-everything-threads\">https://github.com/webassembly/shared-everything-threads</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 590577389,
        "sender_full_name": "RFC notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1776982376
    },
